}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":5,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":18,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":27,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Rede was born in 1310, in Chillingham, Northumberland, England, his father, William Reade, was 42 and his mother, Margaret Towley, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Sarah Reed. He died in 1353, in Northumberland, England, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1310–1353":"1310–1353","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1330–1385":"1330–1385","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1336–1382":"1336–1382","1268–1325":"1268–1325","1280–1310":"1280–1310","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","1382":"1382","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1336":"1336","1268":"1268","1310":"1310","1453":"1453","1353":"1353","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Chillingham, Northumberland, England":"Chillingham, Northumberland, England","England":"England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1310–1353":"1310–1353","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1330–1385":"1330–1385","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1336–1382":"1336–1382","1268–1325":"1268–1325","1280–1310":"12